{
  "texts": [
    "The definitions and computation methodologies of these specific indicators are elucidated as follows:1.",
    "Part-of-Speech Tagging: The indicator for measuring the effectiveness of part-of-speech tagging is the accuracy, which is a ratio of the number of correctly labeled samples to the total number of samples.",
    "The higher the accuracy, the better the word segmentation performance of the model. 2.",
    "NER: The following three common metrics have been selected as the key criteria: precision, recall, and F1-score.",
    "Precision metric indicates the proportion of predicted results that are truly positive."
  ]
}